The area

Address
Neighborhood: Poblenou
The futuristic Agbar Tower stands out from Barcelona's skyline in Poblenou. It is no coincidence then that this area of town is the newly crowned technological park of the city, its own mini Silicon Valley containing a tech incubator (Barcelona Activa) as well as a host of local and international high tech companies. To accommodate the onrush of new residents and workers, the area of Poblenou has seen a surge of activity in new high-rise residential buildings and two top-notch shopping centers catering to everyone's need. The ambiance of this area is calmer than the city center and the beautifully relaxing Bogatell Beach, popular with locals, is just a handful of blocks away.

    Bogatell Beach in Barcelona is a fantastic spot for beachgoers seeking a lively yet relaxed atmosphere.
    This beautiful stretch of sand offers clear waters and plenty of space to unwind or enjoy beach activities. The promenade is lined with charming cafes and restaurants, providing the perfect backdrop for a delightful meal or drink. It's a great place for families, friends, and solo travelers to soak up the sun, play volleyball, or simply enjoy the vibrant Mediterranean vibe. With clean facilities and stunning views, Bogatell Beach is a must-visit for anyone looking to enjoy Barcelona's coastal charm.

Nice beach but I preferred Nova Icaria
Jul 2024 • Family
My daughter and I (16yrs) visited this beach. We were there in the morning. There are toilets, lifeguards, and food and drink huts. Sunbeds were 20 euro each so we laid on our towels instead. There were women coming round asking if you wanted massages, and men selling beach towels. The women came up to us 5 times despite us saying no! The police come around on their beach buggy from time to time...the men bury the towels in the sand then come back for them! We went for lunch then went next door to Nova Icaria beach. Slightly smaller, but no-one tried to sell us massages. I preferred Nova Icaria.
